<h2 class="nounderline"><a name="maincontent">India</a></h2>

<p>
Greetings. This Web site is for you, the parent of a child with a disability who lives in India. We hope you will find it useful.
</p>
<p>
India has laws, government ministries, non-governmental organizations (NGOs), and corporations that can help your child and your family. Your challenge, as a parent, is to learn about the available resources.
</p>
<p>
This Web site will help you do that. It has information about the resources, as 
well as laws affecting children with disabilities, family involvement, advocacy for children with disabilities, 
and information about various disabilities. In addition, the site can connect you to the experiences of other parents of children with disabilities in India and across the world.
</p>
<p>
We hope you will visit often and use the materials. Knowing about available opportunities can make a difference 
in your child's life. 
</p>

<p>
Questions? Please register in our <a href="../intlguestbook.asp">guest book</a> and fill out the section "Can we assist you in some way?" Someone from PACER will contact you! 
</p>
